  "blocks": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 1,
      "text": "Input shaft thrust clearance adjustment"
    },
    {
      "type": "attention",
      "items": [
        "When replacing the transmission case, torque converter case, input shaft assembly, thrust needle bearing, input shaft holder, stator shaft, input shaft holder input shaft bearing, or input shaft bearing, be sure to Thrust clearance must be adjusted."
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Thrust clearance adjustment"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "587_3.0_jpn_11582434_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "587_3.0_jpn_11582435_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Press the forward clutch assembly with a force of 68.6 N (7.0 kgf), measure the depth (C) from the transmission case end surface (A) to the top surface (B) of the forward clutch assembly, and record the measured value."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "587_3.0_jpn_11582436_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "587_3.0_jpn_11582437_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "2",
      "text": "Measure the height (C) from the end surface (A) of the torque converter case to the top surface (B) of the stator shaft and record the measurement. To bring the thrust clearance within the standard value, obtain a calculated value from the following formula based on the measurements in Step 1 and Step 2, and select a 43 x 54.5 mm thrust shim that corresponds to the calculated value. Formula: calculated value = Measured value of step 1 C - Measured value of step 2 C Example.) Measured value of step 1 C: 12.57 mm Measured value of step 2 C: 7.07mm calculated value ＝12.57mm－7.07mm ＝5.50mm Therefore, in this example, shim E is selected."
    },
