    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "4",
      "text": "Install the knock pin (A). Install the torque converter case and tighten the mounting bolts two to three times."
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "587_3.0_jpn_11582439_3.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "6",
      "text": "Attach the magnetic stand base to the torque converter case. Set the dial gauge (A) on the end of the input shaft (B). Pull up the input shaft and measure the clearance. Clearance should be measured at least 3 places at equal intervals. Clearance standard value: 0.11-0.24mm If the measured value deviates from the standard value, adjust the clearance again."
    }
  ],
